<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 12 at 4:59PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT...
WEATHER...
* Widespread moderate to heavy snow will continue through the
evening.
* Snowfall rates around an inch and a half per hour are likely
with the heavier snow through 7 PM. These stronger snow rates
have led to accumulation on untreated roadways with
temperatures between 32 to 33 degrees.
* Northeast winds around 20 mph with gusts 35 mph. Highly
fluctuating visibilities down to a quarter-mile are expected
given the breezy conditions and high snow rates.
IMPACTS...
* Accumulating snow will lead to slippery roads, particularly on
bridges, exit ramps and overpasses.
* Heavy snow will bring a reduction in visibility down to a
quarter-mile.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
